	<http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P78_is_identified_by> "Alongside Anthony and Pachomius, he ranks among the most illustrious Egyptian desert fathers.\n               In Ethiopian tradition he is featured in various translated monastic collections such as Zenā ʾabaw qǝddusān or Collectio Monastica and in the so-called\n               monastic genealogies. He is also venerated as saint and mentioned in the Synaxary.\n                  Not to be confused with his contemporary Macarius of Alexandria.\n               " .
